ce:section.ce:para:
The GQDs used in the experiment were synthesized by hydrothermal process using CA as the carbon source as well as Hexachlorocyclophosphazene as the nitrogen and phosphorous source. Firstly, 1 g CA was added to a 100 ml beaker with a mixture of 50 ml EtOH:H2O (3:1) and stirred for 10 min to obtain a homogeneous system (solution 1). In another 100 ml beaker, 0.05 g Hexachlorocyclophosphazene was dissolved in 20 ml absolute ethanol and stirred for 15 min (solution 2). Subsequently, the two solutions were mixed in a Teflon lined autoclave and the reactor was sealed. Hydrothermal process was carried out in an oven and the temperature increased to 180 °C and kept for 12 h. Finally the reactor was cooled down to room temperature and the product was centrifuged at 4000 RPM to remove any heavy solid particles (schematic of synthesis process is illustrated in Scheme 1
                        ). Three samples with different PNT concentrations was prepared in this way. Table 1
                         sets out the experimental parameters.
